  "riddle": "1. Seek the fortress with a star shape that gazes over hill and vale; from which year do its stone walls whisper tales of bravery?\n\n2. What height do these steadfast walls rise above the earth, measured in meters? \n\n3. As the travelers come and go, what star rating do they bestow upon this historic landmark?\n\n4. Take the number of meters high from clue 2 and combine it with the travelers' rating from clue 3 to find a new total.\n\n5. A great subcontinent lies beyond. What number tells of the souls counted under its vast skies?\n\n6. From the population you just found, uncover the sum of its distinct prime factors to explore deeper connections.\n\n7. As you make your final calculations, compute the absolute difference between 1792 and the height from clue 2, then find the remainder when divided by 10. What single digit does this arithmetic reveal to you?",
